<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-25T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-25T03:00:00-05:00" n="867" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/153: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-25T17:00:00+09:00">March 25, 1935—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 25—9:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>63. Department’s 44, March 22, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>The British Embassy today received a reply from the Foreign Office
                                to its formal representations of November 24 on the subject of the
                                oil monopoly in Manchuria. The reply restates the Japanese stand as
                                communicated previously to the American and British Embassies and
                                further deals with Manchukuo’s alleged non-responsibilities under
                                the treaties between China and other countries. While the reply has
                                not yet been translated it seems to be unconciliatory in
                                tone.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>This Embassy has not yet received its reply although it is
                                momentarily expected. When received and translated we shall
                                telegraph the text or a digest thereof with our suggestions as to
                                further steps.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
